		<h2>Summary</h2>
		<ul>

		<li><span class="info">12</span> papers in <span class="info">9</span> bundles</li>
				<li>Top 3 popular topics:
			<ul>
				<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a> (<span class="info">8</span> times)</li>
				<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a> (<span class="info">6</span> times)</li>
				<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a> (<span class="info">6</span> times)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Top 3 coauthors:
			<ul>
				<li><a href="TedKaminski.html"><span class="info">Ted Kaminski</span></a> (<span class="info">3</span> times)</li>
				<li><a href="LucasKramer.html"><span class="info">Lucas Kramer</span></a> (<span class="info">3</span> times)</li>
				<li><a href="LijeshKrishnan.html"><span class="info">Lijesh Krishnan</span></a> (<span class="info">2</span> times)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
<li>Made <span class="info">23</span> contributions (see below)</li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<h2>List of contributions</h2>
		<ul>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2008/index.html">SLE 2008</a>)</span> Served as a <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2008/Committees.html">Programme Chair</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2009/index.html">SLE 2009</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2009/paper13.html">Verifiable Parse Table Composition for Deterministic Parsing</a></em> (<a href="../profile/AugustSchwerdfeger.html">August Schwerdfeger</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2010/index.html">SLE 2010</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2010/Committees.html">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2011/index.html">SLE 2011</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2011/paper13.html">Integrating Attribute Grammar and Functional Programming Language Features</a></em> (<a href="../profile/TedKaminski.html">Ted Kaminski</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2011/index.html">SLE 2011</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2011/Committees.html">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012/index.html">SLE 2012</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2012/paper03.html">Termination Analysis for Higher-Order Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/LijeshKrishnan.html">Lijesh Krishnan</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012/index.html">SLE 2012</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2012/paper19.html">Modular Well-Definedness Analysis for Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/TedKaminski.html">Ted Kaminski</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012/index.html">SLE 2012</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2012/Committees.html">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2012s/index.html">SLE 2012 SI</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2012s/paper06.html">Monolithic and modular termination analyses for higher-order attribute grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/LijeshKrishnan.html">Lijesh Krishnan</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2013/index.html">SLE 2013</a>)</span> Served as a <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2013/Committees.html">General Chair</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014/index.html">SLE 2014</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2014/paper16.html">Origin Tracking in Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/KevinWilliams.html">Kevin Williams</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014/index.html">SLE 2014</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://www.sleconf.org/2014/Committees.html">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2014s/index.html">SLE 2014 SI</a>)</span> Served as an <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cl.2015.08.009">Editor</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2016/index.html">SLE 2016</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://conf.researchr.org/committee/sle-2016/sle-2016-papers-program-committee">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2017/index.html">SLE 2017</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2017/paper11.html">Ensuring non-interference of composable language extensions</a></em> (<a href="../profile/TedKaminski.html">Ted Kaminski</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2017/index.html">SLE 2017</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://conf.researchr.org/committee/sle-2017/sle-2017-sle-2017-organizing-committee">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2020/index.html">SLE 2020</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2020/paper19.html">Strategic Tree Rewriting in Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/LucasKramer.html">Lucas Kramer</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2020/index.html">SLE 2020</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2020/paper21.html">Monadification of Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/DawnMichaelson.html">Dawn Michaelson</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2020/index.html">SLE 2020</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://conf.researchr.org/committee/sle-2020/sle-2020-papers-program-committee">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2022/index.html">SLE 2022</a>)</span> Served on <a href="https://2022.splashcon.org/committee/sle-2022-program-committee">PC</a></li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2023/index.html">SLE 2023</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2023/paper05.html">Sharing Trees and Contextual Information: Re-imagining Forwarding in Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/LucasKramer.html">Lucas Kramer</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2023/index.html">SLE 2023</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2023/paper06.html">Nanopass Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/NathanRingo.html">Nathan Ringo</a>, <a href="../profile/LucasKramer.html">Lucas Kramer</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li>
<li><span class="info">(<a href="../sle2025/index.html">SLE 2025</a>)</span> <em>Coauthored <a href="../sle2025/paper03.html">Scheduling the Construction and Interrogation of Scope Graphs Using Attribute Grammars</a></em> (<a href="../profile/LukeBessant.html">Luke Bessant</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html"><span class="info">Eric Van Wyk</span></a>) </li></ul>
